text.section:
A holder may charge the buyer the following charges or fees:
Subject to the provisions of § 12-630 of this subtitle, the time balance of an installment sale agreement;
If allowed by a court as costs, the official fees paid to a public official in connection with a proceeding to:
Recover possession of the goods;
Enforce any obligation of the buyer or his surety; or
Realize on any security interest or collateral security;
If no charge was made in the agreement on account of the insurance for the period covered, the premiums for insurance as provided by § 12-613 of this subtitle;
The amount paid for copies of agreements and statements of accounts pursuant to § 12-621 of this subtitle;
Charges permitted by:
§§ 12-623 and 12-626 of this subtitle for delinquencies and repossession expenses; and
Law for extensions and refunds; and
An amount not exceeding $15 if payment is made with a check that is dishonored on the second presentment.
